3.10	Water_Curses	Water Curses	Water Curses is an EP by Animal Collective released in May 2008 on compact disc. 12" vinyl format was released on June 3. The first three tracks were recorded during the band's Strawberry Jam sessions in January 2007 and were produced by Scott Colburn. The EP's fourth and final track, "Seal Eyeing", was recorded at Nicholas Vernhes' Rare Book Room Studio in Brooklyn, New York. Vernhes was also charged with the mixing duties for all four tracks. According to a press release issued by the band, Water Curses "find Animal Collective exploring strange new waters."	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/9/94/Water_Curses_EP.jpg/220px-Water_Curses_EP.jpg
